&lt;p&gt;FastCDC solves two problems, one is to further improve throughput, and the other is to standardize block sizes in the 4KiB-16KiB range. It skips the first 4KiB without having to compute the hash, and its mask is also standardized to be bitwise, so that when it reaches 16KiB, it immediately gets the breakpoint, whether it meets the breakpoint condition or not. In addition, to achieve an average size of 8KiB, he uses different masks to generate breakpoints in 4K-8K and 8K-16K.&lt;/p&gt;
